      • minimum

        public static <E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>> E minimum(E[] data)
        Finds the minimum value in the passed array. NOTE: The array does not need to be completely populated. All relevant data to be processed starts at index 0. Unused elements will be null and should not be considered in computations. Once the first null is encountered it is assumed remaining elements are unused.
        Type Parameters:
        E - Type of data passed. The type must implement the Comparable interface.
        Parameters:
        data - Collection of data to find minimum value of.
        Returns:
        Minimum value in passed data.

      • average

        public static <N extends java.lang.Number> java.lang.Double average(N[] data)

Unused elements will be null and should not be considered in computations. Once the first null is encountered it is assumed remaining elements are unused.
        Type Parameters:

        Returns:
        Average of passed data. Regardless of type passed will always return a Double.
